  "prompt": "How do you use the word paraphrase in a sentence?",
  "response": "Certainly! The word \"paraphrase\" can be used both as a verb and a noun. Here are examples of each:\n\n**As a Verb:**\n- *When writing your essay, make sure to **paraphrase** the sources to avoid plagiarism.*\n- *She **paraphrased** his explanation to make it easier for the class to understand.*\n\n**As a Noun:**\n- *Can you provide a **paraphrase** of the main points discussed in the meeting?*\n- *The teacher asked the students to write a **paraphrase** of the assigned reading.*\n\nUsing \"paraphrase\" correctly helps convey information clearly while demonstrating understanding of the original material.",
